inscription.text: Although the Snowdon pattern gauge is in use, the Beacon Stoop rainfall values must, nevertheless, be regarded with considerable caution, owing to driving snow and heavy gales. In consequence, the minimum index-needle became occasionally displaced; but 20C as the lowest value may be, I think, safely accepted. C. L. W.
